D-Water-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>“The flowing layers of color on the Water frame are inspired by the shifting blues of Icelandic lakes. This flow also takes place in the digital world through the binary code of 1’s and 0’s. Binary 1’s and 0’s create the Specialized downtube logo and the S head tube badge. When translated to English, the binary reads “Nature Digital Nature Digital. . .” over and over again.”</p><figure><figure id=\"attachment_251666\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251666\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail.jpg\" alt=\"Chisel LTD Water digital detail\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Chisel-LTD-Water-Detail-630x420.jpg 630w\"><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251666\">The Specialized logo is made up of 1’s and 0’s with a hidden message</figcaption></figure></figure><p>Each Chisel LTD frame comes with a 64 page collector’s book that showcases the art, words, and inspiration for the Disrupt the Decay series from the designers Kayla and Tom. I had the chance to chat with them about the project and they are stoked to be able to offer this level of graphics treatment on a more accessible platform like the Chisel, with a theme that all riders – regardless of gender or age can relate to. The inclusion of the collector’s book gives each frame a personal touch straight from the designers featuring words and illustrations from the graphics development.</p><p>The Chisel LTD framesets are offered in Specialized’s progressive XC geometry sizing from XS to XL at an MSRP of $1500. Specialized limited edition colorways have a history of selling out fast, so head to <a href=\"https://www.specialized.com/us/en/chisel-ltd-frameset/p/199357?color=319088-199357&amp;searchText=71721-7101&amp;gclid=EAIaIQobChMIgtL52tDz7gIVhYbACh0WPgk8EAQYAiABEgII5_D_BwE\">www.Specialized.com</a> or your local Specialized stocking dealer to get one!</p><div><p><em>All photos courtesy of Specialized by Collin Chappelle</em></p></div></div></div>","author":"Chris Chou","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b0118111fc2dea985bab42b039c62051821294d3f62e7e9532306ad7f7e27c26","category":"Cycling"}